<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - CRANKCASE (Reconditioning) - CRANKSHAFT AND MAIN BEARINGS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CRANKSHAFT AND MAIN BEARINGS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspection</title>
            <para>Check Crankcase Integrity as follows:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate engine so the main bearing saddles are facing upward.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wipe main bearing saddle using a lint-free cloth. The supports must be free of oil.
                    <emph type="bold">DO NOT LUBRICATE THE BACK SIDE OF THE BEARING INSERTS.</emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install upper bearing inserts into bearing saddle. Be sure the locking tangs on the
                    bearings are snapped into the crankcase. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050749">7.49</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050748" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1665" filename="../figeg1/EG1665.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.48.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050749" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12187" filename="../figcg1/CG12187.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.49.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Prussian Blue(r) to the crankshaft main bearing journals. Carefully lower the
                    crankshaft onto the main bearing inserts in the crankcase.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not install the main bearing caps and lower bearing inserts at this time.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft 1/2 turn.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully remove the crankshaft and inspect the upper bearing inserts for an even
                    transfer of bluing from the journals to the bearings.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>IF VOIDS APPEARED IN THE BLUING TRANSFER, THE CRANKCASE INTEGRITY IS QUESTIONABLE.</para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When satisfied that the crankcase is in good order and free of distortion and burrs
                    around the upper bearing insert seats, clean all Prussian Blue(r) from the bearings and crankshaft
                    journals.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
